**TL;DR: What Is a Round Cut Diamond and Should You Buy One?**

A round cut diamond — formally called a **round brilliant cut diamond** — is a circular diamond featuring 57 or 58 precisely arranged facets designed to maximize light return, fire, and scintillation simultaneously. It is the most popular, most studied, and most expensive diamond shape in the world.

**Live May 2026 price snapshot:**

-   1ct natural G-VS1 Excellent Cut GIA starts at **[$3,200](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28915027?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.  
    
-   1ct natural G-VVS2 Excellent Cut GIA starts at **[$3,760](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27622805?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.  
    
-   1ct lab-grown D-IF Ideal Cut IGI: **[$1,560](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28023534?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.  
    
-   1ct lab-grown D-FL Ideal Cut GIA: **[$4,500](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27303352?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.  
    
-   Round brilliants command **25–40% more** than equivalent fancy shapes at the same carat, color, and clarity.

**Buy a round cut diamond if:**

-   Maximum light performance is your priority.  
    
-   You want the most universally recognized engagement ring shape.  
    
-   You want the easiest diamond to resell on the secondary market.  
    
-   You prefer timeless over trendy.

**Consider a fancy shape if:**

-   Budget is your primary constraint — oval and cushion deliver 85–95% of round brilliance at 20–30% less.  
    
-   You want more apparent size per carat — oval and marquise appear 10–15% larger.  
    
-   You want a distinctive look that stands apart from the majority.  
    

> 
> 
> "The round brilliant is the only diamond shape that has been mathematically optimized for over 100 years. Every other shape is beautiful. The round brilliant is engineered. That engineering commands a premium — and for buyers who prioritize optical performance above all else, that premium is justified. For buyers who prioritize value, understanding exactly what the round premium buys is the most important calculation in the purchase." — Farzana Hasan, **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**
