</a></strong></td><td><strong>10/10 for Optics.</strong> The $30 premium over the cluster often points to superior symmetry or a "None" fluorescence grade paired with a 56-57% table, maximizing the stone’s fire.</td></tr><tr><td>26862123</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26862123?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$5,090</a></strong></td><td><strong>10/10. The Clean Silhouette.</strong> Likely features an Excellent polish/symmetry combination that produces the "Hearts and Arrows" light pattern sought by high-end enthusiasts.</td></tr><tr class="highlight-row"><td>28923999</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28923999?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$5,090</a></strong></td><td><strong>10/10. The Top Choice.</strong> The newest listing in the group. At $5,090, you are securing the peak of natural G-VVS2 quality before entering the branded Super-Ideal price brackets.</td></tr></tbody></table>

