**The extraordinary data point:** A lab-grown E-FL Ideal Cut round at $2,380 — Flawless clarity, E color, Ideal cut proportions — costs $820 less than a natural G-VS1 Excellent Cut at $3,200.

You are buying three grades better clarity (FL vs VS1), one grade better color (E vs G), and comparable or superior cut performance — for less money. The only difference is origin.

As documented in the **[lab-grown vs natural diamond price analysis](https://diamondcritics.com/lab-grown-vs-natural-diamond-price/)**, lab-grown prices have collapsed 68% since 2020. For round brilliant buyers who do not require natural origin, the value equation has fundamentally shifted.

> 
> 
> "A lab-grown E-FL Ideal Cut round at $2,380 versus a natural G-VS1 Excellent at $3,200. The lab stone is chemically identical — same carbon atom structure, same 57 facets, same optical properties. The GIA cannot distinguish them without laboratory testing. The $820 difference pays for geological age and mining history. In 2026, that is a conscious, deliberate choice — not a default." — Farzana Hasan
> 
> 

