> "The round brilliant has been mathematically optimized for over 100 years. Every proportion, every angle, every facet relationship has been studied, modeled, and refined. The result is a diamond that returns more light through the table than any other shape — a performance advantage that is real, measurable, and visible. Whether that advantage is worth 30% more than an oval depends entirely on your priorities. Know what you are buying, buy it with the right proportions, and the round brilliant will never disappoint." — Farzana Hasan, **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**
